-- Russian Equity Movers: Norilsk, Polyus Gold International, UTair
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-04-02T14:08:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/russian-equity-movers-norilsk-polyus-gold-international-utair.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slipped 0.2
percent to 1,514.74 at 5:50 p.m. in Moscow, after earlier
gaining 1.3 percent. The dollar-denominated RTS Index lost 0.1
percent to 1,636.58.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis:  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN)  (GMKN RX), the world’s biggest
producer of the metal, fell 1.1 percent to 5,341 rubles, poised
for the lowest since Jan. 11, after HSBC Holdings Plc cut its
recommendation to neutral from overweight.  Polyus Gold International Ltd. (PLGL)  (PLGL LI) declined after the
Russian miner’s 2011 earnings missed analyst’s estimates,
dropping as much as 1.3 percent before trading 0.3 percent lower
at $3.07 in  London .  UTair Aviation (UTAR)  (UTAR RX), the Russian aviation group, slid
the most in three months after one of its planes crashed in the
Tyumen region, killing at least 31 of the 43 passengers and crew
on board. The shares fell 4.1 percent lower at 19.55 rubles, the
most since Jan. 3 on a closing basis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
